resources.string: Drag the reject call with message panel upwards to send a call-reject message as you reject an incoming call.
Tap the answer call button to answer a call.
Tap the reject call button to reject a call.
Swipe the answer button from left to right to answer a call.
Swipe the reject button from right to left to reject a call.
Tap the keypad button to enter numbers during a call.
Tap the speaker button to turn on the speakerphone.
Tap the mute button to mute all sound from your end of the call.
Tap the Bluetooth button to continue a call on a connected Bluetooth device.
Tap the end call button to end a call.
Tap the extra volume button to increase the volume.
Tap the add call button to call another person and add them to the current call.
Conferencing is only available for voice calls.
Video calling requires the use of both data and voice minutes over the mobile network. Charges may apply.
Data limit that you have set on your phone has reached and data is turned off. Video call requires a data connection. Turn on mobile data or connect to any available Wi-Fi network.
Emergency calls over Wi-Fi not allowed in this location.
Unable to switch to video call. Battery low.
%s cannot receive video calls at this time. You will now be connected through a voice call.
To turn off the speakerphone, open the flip phone.
Tap RECORDINGS to view your recorded calls.
The last call or message to or from this number did not use the preferred SIM card for calls. Select which SIM card to use.
Switched to voice call because of request from called party.
%s wants to switch to video call.

"We tried, but we can’t switch your video call to Wi-Fi at this time.
Your video call is still running on the mobile network. (Data usage applies if you choose to continue.)"

"The Wi-Fi signal was not strong enough to continue your video call.
Your video call is now running on the mobile network. (Data usage applies if you choose to continue.)"
